rComments: For this class we had 3 projects that we could do either in group or alone, and the final exam. Be aware that she's a tough grader for the projects. The final was all multiple choices and cumulative. The amount of slides we had to study for the final was huge. The final was hard and very specific.

The subject wasn't well teach, missing organization and preparation. Plus, the teacher teach everything in the most complicated way possible. The notes were not relevant to the questions in the final exam. Not the best experience in my university studies.

Very passionate and interesting prof overall for a late night class. She makes the student participate, even though it was a big class, which is kind of nice for once. No books have to be bought which is nice. 2 written projects we're fairly easy, the final exam was fair but long and all multiple choice! The best prof I've had in 2 years at Uottawa
Dr. Garcia's exams were fair however I did not feel that she was really committed to the class because of her many other duties as dean. She can be very condescending at times and quite stubborn.
Bonne prof! Même si la communication en santé n'est pas mon sujet de prédilection, elle a sut m'intéresser. Cependant, il faut bien apprendre les notes de cours pour l'examen.
